description: Returns an overview of the members of a group. Users and groups can be members of a group.

parameters.name: OrganizationId
parameters.description: The identifier for the organization under which the group exists.

parameters.name: GroupId
parameters.description: The identifier for the group to which the members (users or groups) are associated. The identifier can accept GroupId, Groupname, or email. The following identity formats are available: Group ID: 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012 or S-1-1-12-1234567890-123456789-123456789-1234 Email address: group@domain.tld Group name: group.

nested_items.name: Members
nested_items.description: The members associated to the group.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: A member can be a user or group.

nested_items.name: State
nested_items.description: The state of the member, which can be ENABLED, DISABLED, or DELETED.

nested_items.name: EnabledDate
nested_items.description: The date indicating when the member was enabled for WorkMail use.

nested_items.name: DisabledDate
nested_items.description: The date indicating when the member was disabled from WorkMail use.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token to use to retrieve the next page of results. The first call does not contain any tokens.
